# Contracts-first (no drift between Node and Python)

The single source of truth for every cross-service shape is `contracts/`:
`openapi.node.yaml`, `openapi.rag.yaml`, `jobs.schema.json`.

- To change any request/response/job shape: **edit `contracts/` → run codegen → use the generated
  types.** TS types land in `packages/shared-types`; Pydantic models land in `packages/py-core`.
- **Never hand-write or hand-edit generated types.** They will be overwritten.
- **Never guess a shape** — read `contracts/` (or the generated types) instead.
- If Node and Python disagree at runtime, fix the contract or codegen, not a local patch.

See `docs/development-workflow.md` §3 and ADR `docs/adr/0001-monorepo-and-contracts-first.md`.

> `contracts/` is scaffolded with placeholder skeletons (`openapi.node.yaml`, `openapi.rag.yaml`,
> `jobs.schema.json`). This rule is mandatory as soon as real shapes are defined there.
